War, the US wasn't all that

00:02:00.430 --> 00:02:03.655
strong a science power.

00:02:03.655 --> 00:02:05.530
There were countries
like Germany and Britain

00:02:05.530 --> 00:02:07.150
that were considerably
further ahead

00:02:07.150 --> 00:02:12.270
by general world view in
science capability than the US.

00:02:12.270 --> 00:02:17.665
And Vannevar Bush worked
hard during World War II

00:02:17.665 --> 00:02:22.210
to build up that early
stage research capability

00:02:22.210 --> 00:02:24.610
and then link it to
more applied stations

00:02:24.610 --> 00:02:26.120
of the course of the war.

00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:28.510
At the end of the
war, he has a choice.

00:02:28.510 --> 00:02:30.000
What do we save?

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:32.570
And he decides as the
war is winding down--

00:02:32.570 --> 00:02:34.630
and we'll talk about
this next week.

00:02:34.630 --> 00:02:38.530
--he decides to save
that early stage research

00:02:38.530 --> 00:02:41.350
capability because that
was what the problem was.

00:02:41.350 --> 00:02:45.370
The United States was
king of manufacturing.

00:02:45.370 --> 00:02:48.280
Manufacturing production
capability in the United States

00:02:48.280 --> 00:02:52.180
dwarfed every other country,
including our two major postwar

00:02:52.180 --> 00:02:55.670
or pre-war competitors,
Germany and Japan.

00:02:55.670 --> 00:03:00.490
We just had much bigger
production capability.

00:03:00.490 --> 00:03:02.530
We had developed mass
production we would read.

00:03:02.530 --> 00:03:06.040
No one else had figured out,
in part because we could sell

00:03:06.040 --> 00:03:07.660
into a continent size economy.

00:03:07.660 --> 00:03:12.970
We created the first continent
sized industrial economy,

00:03:12.970 --> 00:03:14.300
and we could sell into that.

00:03:14.300 --> 00:03:17.380
So production
wasn't the problem.

00:03:17.380 --> 00:03:19.180
We completely
dominated production.

00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:21.417
It never occurred
to anybody in the US

00:03:21.417 --> 00:03:23.500
that there might come a
challenge to US production

00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:24.550
capability.

00:03:24.550 --> 00:03:28.030
Instead the problem Vannevar
Bush is trying to solve

00:03:28.030 --> 00:03:31.580
is building this early
stage research capability,

00:03:31.580 --> 00:03:34.950
which we didn't really
have that strong

00:03:34.950 --> 00:03:37.330
a system prior to the war.

00:03:37.330 --> 00:03:39.400
So the US innovation
system when it gets

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:41.410
created in that
post-war period--

00:03:41.410 --> 00:03:44.050
and we'll go into
this next week.

00:03:44.050 --> 00:03:49.780
--doesn't focus on production
because it's not a problem.

00:03:49.780 --> 00:03:52.600
In countries like
Germany and Japan--

00:03:52.600 --> 00:03:56.260
which by the way, we had just
bombed their production system.

00:03:56.260 --> 00:03:58.540
They've got to restore all that.

00:03:58.540 --> 00:04:00.160
They've got to rebuild that.

00:04:00.160 --> 00:04:05.440
They develop innovation systems
that are focused on production.

00:04:05.440 --> 00:04:09.100
That's where they focus
the innovation systems.

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:10.340
Not like the US does.

00:04:10.340 --> 00:04:12.730
We think R&D is king.

00:04:12.730 --> 00:04:16.540
Other countries assume this link
between research and production

00:04:16.540 --> 00:04:18.550
and focus on the
production stage

00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:21.103
because it is indeed
highly innovative.

00:04:21.103 --> 00:04:23.270
We just are organizing our
economy very differently.

00:04:23.270 --> 00:04:27.670
We miss that, and the
results are painful.

